replyContent: If everything is displayed twice this means that you are syncing CalenGoo twice with your Google account (via Android and also directly). I.e. you let CalenGoo display all your calendars twice. If you then delete an event, both "copies" will vanish, because it is the same event, just displayed twice. Please contact android@calengoo.com to get help.

content: I‚Äôd give this app 10 stars if that was an option I‚Äôve tried several calendar/tasks apps for Android and for me, Calengoo is hands down the best. I have a fairly demanding requirement wanting to synch Windows computers (Outlook 2013, Mozilla Thunderbird) and Android devices (Samsung Tablet and Motorola phone) around a CalDav server (Horde Groupware). The app works seamlessly. The functionality and the range of views and screen layouts suits me perfectly. Where I want to change things, the configuration options for this app allow a great deal of customisation. I‚Äôve read one or two reviews where the reviewer regards the range of configuration options as quite daunting and that I can understand but Calengoo works very well straight out of the box if one doesn‚Äôt want to get into detail of configuration. And the extra 5 stars? These I would happily give for the quality of support this app gets from its developer. Initially, I encountered an issue around tasks synchronisation that was related to the way in which CalDav is implemented on the Horde server. The developer responded to my enquiry within a couple of hours and from then on was very prompt in providing updates and responses to my feedback until the issue was resolved entirely. This is superb product support. Congratulations Dominique.

content: I've been an avid fan since 2011 when I first bought Calengoo from the Amazon Appstore for my new kindle Gen 1 tablet (there's a blast from the past!). But as time goes on, I am now entrenched in the phone and very little Google desktop usage. it is the perfect app for me. I am a list person and Task lists are ideal for so many things. The calendar functions perfectly with lots of hooks for easy event manipulation. I recently uncovered the New-Event and New-Task widgets that are AWESOME. I love all the display customizations possible. And my settings were easily portable from phone to phone. They may be overwhelming to some (as noted in an earlier review) and maybe the defaults could be improved for new users, but I love all the settings available to get it just right for me. Developer support top notch too! I just reported a small cosmetic bug and I'm sure he will fix it right away. My only suggestion is that I would like to see more icons/emojis to decorate events with and to categorize/filter them so I could remove from my view all the ones not of interest (maps, numbers). Also multiple emojies on an event could be useful.

replyContent: I am sorry but this is a general Google Calendar problem and not related to CalenGoo. CNBC wrote about it yesterday: https://www.cnbc.com/2019/08/27/how-to-stop-google-calendar-spam.html . By default Calengoo just displays what the Android calendar contains. Oh, also the developer is very receptive to feedback!  UPDATE 2018: This is still the best Android calendar app bar none.  Well maintained, and so much fine grained control. When I need to input a new appointment I can copy the original appointment as a new one, simply change the date-time-and notation, and save it before the secretary can hand it to me on a card! I could go on and on. These guys have done an incredible job with an impeccable attention to detail. Yesterday my doctor asked me when I had a certain test done and I had no idea. It was years ago. So, as I have done many times before, I did a simple search, and within a minute gave her the date of my last test two years ago, along with every other time it had been performed, and by whom, going clear back to 2011! Worked great for years then hangs & crashes recently. Now won't open. Uninstalled & reinstalled to no avail. Please fix.
replyContent: Please just contact android@calengoo.com if you have any problems. There wasn't an update of CalenGoo recently so it cannot have been caused by a change in CalenGoo. Just contact me, then I can help you to examine and fix the problem. Thank you very much!

content: Does the best job. Integrates very well with Aquamail. Highly customisable.
Perfect
Very responsive; I lost my license when factory reset my phone and they immediately responded after I emailed them. Couldn't live without it, works perfectly with google's features.

I'd heard a lot about this app, but was put off by the price tag. I don't mind paying for a great app, but I've paid for so many apps that later turned out to be duds. The developer gave me a three day trial and honestly, I only needed an hour to decide. It's got everything I was looking for. The way it handles tasks (specifically syncing with google tasks, which is so elegant), I don't need a separate task manager. It's simple on the top layer, but has so much under the hood in terms of configuration.

Love this app! It's helped me manage the multiple (personally customized) snooze notifications I like to have for my calendar, syncs well with my Google calendar, and the creator was fantastic with customer service when I had a question. All in all, a great app for me!

I'm kinda a calendar geek/freak and did not want to give up my paper calendar. Soon I realized I had too keep up and began my quest trying all calendar apps. For me this is the absolute best  on the market 4 stars because it does need a lunar calendar but you still need to look no further, this is the best out there.

If you loved WeekCal on iPhone you will definitely love this on Android. This app has it all especially when it comes to managing meetings and appointments.  Very robust when it comes to reminders and alarms (and you can even have it send you or others a text message for reminders)   The interface is easy to use and the widgets are outstanding.  I've looked at about 8 other calendar apps for Android and this beats them all.   Also the week view (horizontal) is the best please never change it.
Very customizable with great support.

Had this app for years and love it!   I was  recently tempted by google tasks to try their calender for a few weeks but it's just not as  nice to view or use so I ended up re installing the lovely Calengoo and I'm back to normal.  Thank you for such a cool and simplistic App that helps make sense of a busy life!!  Love  the week to view layout the most..... awesome!! Please don't ever change this .... the design is way better that googles =)
Great calendar

It's syncs for longer than Google calendars 1 year limit.  It's all I needed of an app.  Also comes with good widget for home screen.  Does the job  and costs the same as a McDonald's burger..  Worth every penny.
This calendar app is the best I have used. It combines all my calendars and tasks in one place. I had one slight issue, but Dominique provided excellent support and we got it fixed!
Love this calendar! I use it to seamlessly sync all of our family calendars.

I was looking for a calendar which gave the option of displaying an event's time of day as a fixed time, not changing when my phone changed time zones.I just wanted to be able to look at my calendar events, and see immediately flight times etc, no matter what city they were based in.  I believed CalenGoo could do this, and emailed the dev asking lots of questions. I received a quick, very detailed and  helpful reply.  Excellent calendar, excellent support!

I've used this calendar app for several years now, with no complaints. I tried many others, but quickly return to CalenGoo (despite its odd name). ‚ò∫ One feature I'd like to see improved in its ease of use is switching calendars. I manage (way too) many calendars, and I still find it tedious switching which calendars I want to view. In the native Google calendar app, it's as easy as tapping the "hamburger" menu and clicking each one on and off. So, for that feature alone I pull up the Google app.
I have installed and uninstalled a LOT of calendar apps. I'm sticking with this powerful, highly customizable winner!
Loved it

This App is fully customisable calendar, which makes one's life much easier once set up. Extensive and thorough guides and documentation help to make the most of this app. Worth to spend a penny and invest some time into initial setting.

I've tried lots of calendars that offer sms reminders to clients. This is the only one I've got to work. It works flawlessly (just remember if you have any app killers installed to add this and the sms add on to the ignore list). The only thing that would improve it for me is to be able to include the appointment end time in sms reminders. I'm mobile and arrange appointments to arrive between 2 times and would like to be able to include both times.

Main reason for installing this app was to overcome the Google calendar issue where events entered on a pc for more than a year ahead would not show up on my phone until less than a year away. As a photographer this is important ..however the flexibility and professional Calengoo is impressive and I love it .. and worth the couple of quid they charge.. impressive .. (oh and I never review apps) .. üòÜ

I have tried most calendars available.  I have a very demanding schedule.  Other calendars can't handle it. And the Developer has responded to my emails and made suggested changes to improve how the app handles reminders and the snooze function.  Unbelievable service! Never had this happen before.  Most developers ignore you,  not this one.
Needs better integration with Samsung Note series features such as Air View.
I've been using this for quite a few years now and it's definitely the best diary app available however, it's started repeatedly freezing on my Note 4 and has almost unusable :-(
replyContent: Please contact android@calengoo.com if you have any problems with the app. Then we can examine and fix the freezes. Thank you very much!

content: I lost the little tab/icon that allows me to add items to calendar.  Disappeared a cpuple of days ago and i cannot locate it. Also my tasks are not integrating from google.
replyContent: There are many ways to add items to the calendar, e.g. double tapping a free space in the day view. And if your tasks are not displayed, just add your Google account under "Settings > Tasks". Please just contact android@calengoo.com if you have any problems. Thank you very much!

content: This is a nice calendar. UPDATE: At first I thought that it was unnecessary for me because the calendar in Android 5.0 seemed to do all of the same things, but at present I am using both calendars for various reasons.

Absolutely the best, and I have tried nearly every Calendar app. I needed to have tasks integrated with recurrence and alarms on several devices for the tasks, and manage 3 calendars. Calengoo does it perfectly. And the floating events are brilliant. And the options to configure the app are amazing. You can change probably every configuration in the app. Have used this now for about 36 hours, and still making a few tweaks in the settings, but it is awesome. Could do maybe with a touch of material design in some screens, like the add/edit event and task screen. When you view an event you get a nice coloured screen, but adding an event or task, the screen looks a bit gray.  This app deserves the whole 5 stars, and was worth every single penny.  I have had a few crashes on marshmallow namely after changing a setting, otherwise, the app runs nice.
This app is one I never have to think about. Loads of customizations and easy to use features. It just works.
But could be perfect if included two very important features: 1. Foldable task groups. 2. A chrome extension.
Worth every penny
This calendar app is fantastic. It does everything you could want in every way you can imagine, and then some. I almost don't miss my Treo now.
Most basic link to Microsoft exchange is missing.
By far the best calendar on the Android market. Looks great out of the box but has PLENTY OF CUSTOMIZATIONS. Also, dev responds immediately!
Since the last update.... SO many bugs !!!

This one is the winner!  However there is something you should look at as a little problem. When moving an email to calengoo the calendar will stay open and I cannot get back to inbox or write new email unless I close the calengoo. That is counterproductive. And as I mentioned before be nice to move also txt messages to calengoo

If you like to configure every part of your calendar app like I do, you will love this app. It is the most highly customizable calendar app in the play store. I've tried many and calengoo is with every penny.
Does not notify attendees.  Would give 5th star.  Instead may have to go to another calendar that does.
I've had it for years and it has worked beautifully the whole time. Everytime I get a new phone I download it again.
Ridiculously complex and annoying. That's five quid of my hard earned down the drain
Same problem described by Jem L.
This is a wonderful calendar app. It does everything I want and need it to do, and more. I've been using this app for 4 years and still loving it. Customer service is excellent, too.

I had a lot of trouble using stock Google calendar. Tried this program out and I now I can not do with out it. Don't write reviews often, as I felt I had to share. You can make a widget with a grid to display all upcoming events on your homepage. Very useful imho
LOADS of options. I have used this since it was in beta, and I have yet to find another calendar app with as much to offer.
Very very cool. Extremely customisable. Brings through icons from Google Calendar... Favourite feature lol
Very nice syncs and works with ical on my Blackberry Q10, the layout is so much better than the stock Blackberry calendar, thankyou
This has been the best app for years really easy to use and lots of great widgets. But since the last update it just keeps crashing. It won't let me add any new events or tasks. Please fix this!
replyContent: Please send an email to android@calengoo.com so that I can help you to fix the problem. No one else reported such crashes so it is probably a specific problem with your configuration. Please just send me a short email, then I can help you to get it correctly running again! I am glad that you like it and would like to help you to fix the problem!

content: Formely a Palm OS user, Calengoo reminds me of "datebk6", a full-blown calendar app back in 2007. Calengoo is now one of the main reasons I never go back to Palm. Three thumbs up for the developer!

If for no other reason than to finally take control of a fully-customizable calendar notification, you need to install CalenGoo. Look, this is a specialized recommendation. From the notification you want, to fully-configurable snooze periods, CalenGoo delivers. Sure, check out the other features, of which CalenGoo has some unique ones. But just for the notification and snooze capabilities, CalenGoo cannot be beat. It's the features Android should have, baked in.
Much better than the standard calendar app that comes with the phone.
I love the agenda widget and Google tasks integration. Just chock full of features. However it needs support for the new Google calendar reminders.
Checkable tasks show on all the views by due date. It also has the option to have overdue tasks show on today. A must-have app with great looking widgets as well.
This is a superb app. Constantly being tweaked making it better & better all the time. Excellent developer support. Worth the money

My main motivation for buying this was to get drag-and-drop functionality to move events from one day to another. Calengoo has this ability and it's smooth.  There is an almost overwhelming amount of complexity and configurability in this product, but this is actually refreshing given the degree to which Google's official Calendar app has become a Fisher-Price¬Æ toy.  The out-of-the-box defaults are adequate, and appearance can be configured to suit personal tastes with only a minor bit of menu exploration.
Use is constantly for about 3 years now. Occasiosal sync glitches but all in all a wonderful tool.
This app outclasses everything else out there.  Well worth the money. The developer is very dedicated and responsive. I highly recommend this app.
I love it. Very customizable.  Only problem: Done tasks are not saved in history. Neither can I make them visible through selecting the option for showing crossed-out.

2/17/16 Update: I continue to try and find a better calendar/todo app but always come back to this one.   It's still the best out there.   Went away for awhile and just came back to find a totally updated look and lots more functionality.  Wow, very nice.  Additionally, there is no better support out there.  I recently emailed developer twice and received both replys in less than 12 hours.  Detailed ones not canned ones.  You can't go wrong with this calendar/todo app.  Highly recommend!

userName: Ronda-Grace Dorval, M.B.A. Business and RE Analyst
content: been using this calendar for years and it just keeps getting better. it can do everything and it does "everything" superbly well!! I would pay $100 bucks for this!

Very configurable and font size can be made bigger for those with poor vision. However all the options do make it complex to configure. However it works and once you have how you want it it is stable.  First used on an HTC Desire HD and now a Samsung S6. Well worth the money, especially if you are a Google users as well.
This is just getting better and better! The customer support was quick and very effective. We can only wish for its good continuity. Thanks CalenGoo for making our lives easier!

Fantastic support.  Developer attended to my issues and resolved it within one day! I especially like the feature to set different type of recurring appointments, as many calendar apps do not offer beyond the basic.  The task feature even allow you have parent task and 2nd level, 3rd level, etc sub tasks.  Overall, great. I purchased the app. Expecting even more features in the near future. Highly recommended.

I've been using both iOS and Android versions of this app since I started using smart phones and tablets and no calendar app has ever surpassed Calengoo's easy to use features. It has all the features that I need and truly makes me efficiently productive. Kudos to Dominique! üëè can't wait for your Windows 10 version! Please make one!
I've used this app for years and love it! Easy to use, very useful widgets to fit any user preference. Stable and quick.

I wanted an app that provided a quick and easy way to create and move around schedules and I found it in this program. It provides the slickest drag and drop off all of those I tested. It's extremely easy to read and the title is clearly visible allowing one to preview without having to open or zoom in the individual schedule ( two finger zoom is supported ). In short it's a competent and complete app featuring a ton of settings while retaining a friendly user interface. Easily one of my favorite apps.
Good job

I've been a long time user of this app, it's feature rich and has everything you think you need for a calendar app and more. I love being able to tweak all the options and then being able to backup those settings. I recently had an issue and contacted the developer, he was great and responded to me quickly with a solution =).
Best app in Google Play!
Excellent.
Great calendar app for integrating with Google. Extremely customizable.

I tried close to 10 other apps trying to find something to sync with my Google tasks, and to have them show up in my calendar on my phone. It still doesn't show up in my Android calendar, but I like the calendar that comes with this even better. I really like being able to see events and tasks in the month view, something the Android calendar didn't do. Well worth what I paid for it. I would've spent at least 4 times as much for a decent planner, and this doesn't have to be replaced ever year.
Can't live without apps. I've been using this app for 4yrs. My favorite feature is the widget on my home screen that tells me the next event in my calendar.
Easily the best
replyContent: Please contact android@calengoo.com so that we can examine your speed issues. Thank you very much!

content: Best calendar so far.

The options on the app are the BEST. UPDATE: I have NEVER updated a review before, heck I hardly ever review anything, but this is so outstanding.  Ive been using this for over 1 yr (& 5 months actually). This is still by far the best. The developer adds new options & features quite frequently and some of those options are ones that I never knew I needed! I use it more times in one day the I can count. Its very handy. I have tried others, but none of them come close to this one. I highly recommend this app!
Thanks, best calendar out there!!!

Having been with a competitor for many years,  finally switched due to total lack of interest on behalf of the developer.  Love this app and the settings options.  Great,  easy to read display.  And FAST email support.  Recommended to anyone who is looking for a great calendar and task app.
Works Flawlessly on Gingerbread

The first app to install on a new device. Very comprehensive and useful, though a bit complicated. Excellent email support,  constant development and improvement. More features than any calendar app I know, on any platform. EXCELLENT.

Still the best android calendar app. In a different league from the rest in terms of customisable options (appearance as well as as fuctionality).  Actively improved and updated by its developer. I can't say enough good things about Calengoo.
Being a full time Nursing student I would never be able to stay on top of all my responsibility's without this app.

This app is truly great.  Lots of customization options,  but easy to use on a daily basis. Reliable and has responsive customer support. Would easily give it 5 stars if only it synced with Outlook Exchange tasks.

Sync with Google Calendar is good. Lots of widgets and customization options. However there is a very long lag when typing every time I edit an event, and it may jumble what is typed. I've been hoping for an update for months now. Please fix.
Like the design. Simple to use.

Have just tried this and like it very much. I had 1 little glitch that turned out to be something w/ Google and not CalenGoo but Dominique got back to me so quickly and was so helpful that I have recommended this app to my friends.

Awesome calendar.. It's powerful.. However widgets not good for some reason at the moment. I'm finding they are going missing, or partially displaying. Agenda widget I finally got working after disabling the scroll feature but it now doesn't update when I change anything in the calendar. Samsung Galaxy 6 Edge.

Used this for years on iPhones, when I moved to Android it was my first must-have app and I wasn't disappointed. Powerful, infinitely customizable, it might be overwhelming at first. But stick with it and explore this app; it will do it all. I live in Agenda view all day long, integrate with company and personal Google calendars, and it runs my life. Developer made the change to auto-dial calls from an event in just a couple of days on request - a conference call must-have.
My advice? Just get it over with...buy it! You will be so pleased. Incredibly adaptive...with zero "glitches"...not even one. Flawless. A dedicated-to-detail masterpiece.
Only app that bridges all the devices. The zoom feature alone is worth it. Having tasks available is a bonus.
This is the app I've been searching for.  Something that would download my entire calendar without a problem.  Thank you.

True it seems comlicated initially due to Lots n lots of options but when u explore it does as you like. I have been using this app since long and tried number of other apps but this is awsome. I have only two issues. I can't attach other format of files  like e pub and there is no option for sub heading

Love the functionality. I was "raised" on DateBK+ through DateBK6 on the old PalmOS and have looked for a suitable replacement since leaving the old Palm platform. Calengoo does the trick. Every update is brilliant. Worth 10 times the price... no... really!

This calendar is hideous. And that's important. I need to see very quickly the information I need to plan my day. This calendar, in every view including all widgets, is quite simple the ugliest calendar ever made. The menu is huge. No one needs all those options. And, you guessed it, it's hideous.

This is so completely well implemented, thoroughly and nicely supported and just plain constantly useful that it is almost impossible to believe. It is a template for software development and for providing value. Thank you, Dominique.
I sent an email requesting a refund. This app doesn't sync tasks from my Samsung Galaxy Note 5 calendar. This was the only reason why I wanted this app. Otherwise it's a good app.

I just love having it back after all this time. Been using the stock calendar app and a decent free app too on my Android phones but nothing quite compares to the customization and feel that Calengoo gives. Developer was always responsive and I see he continues to be. I love how my calendar and tasks display and how I can tweak the colors for variety even. Nice touch. The display of information is a good blend too. It was my lifesaver before and my new one again.
Flexible, highly configurable, well supported power-user calendar app. Top pick for sure!
pity I can't share lists
I've used a ton of calender and task managers, this one is the best.
Allot of effort and work by the Developer to make this calendar app the best! It is worth to buy it. Thanks Dev!

I only wish I could customize the tasks widget. It's too tiny and crammed, and can't be sorted by date added*.  Other than that, Every single feature is customizable. It's almost intimidating, but once you get it right, it's so right. Control freaks and  high performers will understand.  *Sort task by date is helpful because the AMAZING add task by voice feature is great, but I lose those tasks because they default to the bottom off my list and it's hard to find them later to change their priority, etc.
Been using this App for over a year and love it completely. It syncs with all my devices and once you master this App, you'll never look for another one!
Hands down the best calendar app. I use this with extreme alarm clock app

I've been using Calengoo for years now - love the flexibility and options. I can download and display as many calendars as i choose (Google & others), repeat functions, change just one event; many display options. Enlarge from monthly view so you dont have to switch views - but easy to do so if you want.   I am sooo picky when it comes to juggling my calendars and this app does not disappoint!  It is the first app i download on new phones, and easily syncs, so i can just pick up where i left off. Thanks! !
I updated and the widget won't load! Please fix this!! Then I can give you the five stars you deserve
replyContent: Please contact android@calengoo.com if you have problems with the widgets (or any other problems). It probably isn't a bug in CalenGoo but a problem of your Android system that you can fix with a few steps (i.e. uncheck all widgets in CalenGoo under "Settings > Widgets > Available widgets", reboot your phone and check them again).

content: I have used this for years now.  Love the customisation possibilities, works really well.
It's look beautiful. Good design and have many tools for planning . But speed isn't perfect. When I change tabs have some delay before I see  information . I'm hope that it will fix.
I have been using this Calendar app for 5 yrs on Multiple devices. It is still the best ever. The Developer continues to be on top of updates, Great Job.
works fine on a 3.2in screen. thank you!
Been using this app for years. What's not to like. Kudos to the Devs.
Great calendar! Settings allow you to set this up exactly how you want it. Difficult to start out,  but, hey, how else can it do all it can do. Superior!

This is the best calendar available.  I've now been using it for 4 or 5 years and it consistently out performs all the rest of the options out there. It integrates all our family's calendars so I know exactly what everyone is doing and where they are at any time. This is key for a busy mom. It's easy to use and seamless which it a big plus. The customer support is to notch too.

So glad I tried this! I've known about Calengoo through iOS for years but I didn't think a do-it-all app was for me, preferring to separate out my calendar from my task app,although I did try a few PIMs. Since I'm knee-deep in Google apps and need a cross-platform workflow I decided to give Calengoo a try once I discovered it has almost all the features I want!  First off the Material update on Android is beautiful. The UI is very easy to navigate even though there are tons of customizations. There is a learning curve to those. Calengoo also has brilliant Evernote integration which is hard to find, allowing you to attach an EN note to an event or task and syncing with EN Reminders. There are other attachment possibilities. The tasks have their own tab but are also integrated with the calendar. I was never a Google Task person but Calengoo makes it so easy and pleasurable. The 1 thing missing for me is a local desktop app but I hear its being worked on. Highly recommend this app. Really love opening it every day.

I have used this app for a long time, ever since switching from Agendus/Action Names on the old Palm OS. This app features excellent support for event icons, something I really miss on other calendar apps. Being able to have a quick visual overview of events just based on which icon you have assigned to them is invaluable to me. CalenGoo supports event icons better than Google's own Calendar web app; I have to assign icons in CalenGoo because on the web it doesn't even work! Great job, dev! A real treat!
Seriously, use it. One of the few apps I have stuck with through all my different phones.
Good calendar app until last update - now most important part, widget, doesn't load - developer worked it out, so 5 stars it is! Great app and customizable out the wazoo. Love it.
replyContent: I am currently working on the widget problem that some devices have. Can you please contact me under android@calengoo.com ? Thank you very much!

content: I had problems with the widgets for awhile. They contacted me and helped me resolve the issue and got it up and running again. It works like a charm now!
replyContent: If your agenda and task widget does not work correctly, this is probably caused by a bug in your Android system. Please contact android@calengoo.com so that I can send you instructions how to fix it. Your system probably thinks that there are far more instances of these widgets than you are actually using.

content: Simple but with many more options than other apps.
Your dedication for develop this application is admirable.

This app is so nice I've paid for it twice! Once through Amazon, and because I wanted to make sure I had the latest updates I bought it again through Google Play. it is one of the top five apps that I put on my phone when I refresh or get a new one. Infinitely customizable, but it does take some time to go through the vast variety of menu offerings in order to make the app truly yours.   My only complaint is with a combination of how Calengoo interacts with my Note 5. There is no longer a dedicated menu button. On the left of the home button is the 'recently used' button, and a long press brings up the multi window. On the right is the back button and a long press brings up the menu of many applications, but not with Calengoo.  With Calengoo it boots me out of the program altogether. I'm hoping this will be fixed in the future, but as long as I'm able still use three fingers to access the menu I'll be OK.  Thanks for such a great app!
I love the Agenda mode, my over 50 eyesight does too! Couldn't do my job without this calendar to tell me what the plan is!!
I couldn't praise this app more if I tried.
Best calendar .organization app .love it . support is perfect and so very helpful. Thank you so much.is a life changer :)

Great app, great support. I've tried nearly every available calendar app for Android. Many of them are very good. This one is excellent. Options can get a bit dense/complicated for those seeking a simple app. But oh, the flexibility! Pretty much anything you might want to do with a calendar app is available here. It's been reliable and dev answers feedback. Worth a look if you're shopping apps, or wanting more from your calendar.

I've been using CalenGoo for many years, since it first was on the Nokia Internet Tablet/Maemo and it's still the best calendar app. Developer is very quick to reply and help solve problems. Highly recommended!   Edit 9/24 - if you have problem with widget freezing device after update, uninstall/reinstall totally fixed it!
I stick with Android technology largely because I can't do without this calendar.
Best calendar app that I've been able to find.  Does everything I want it to.
An excellent diary / organiser.  Fully sync's with Google.  Powerful features is now my default schedule manager.
Couldn't live without it. Lost all my data installed this and hey presto magically reappeared
BEST CALENDAR app for Android! Keep the improvements coming!
The title says it all. This calendar is the only mobile calendar for me.

EXCELLENT ---so much better than original Droid X calendar. Thanks for your genius!   I've used this great app now for 4-1/2 years to run my life and it just gets better and better.  Dominique is very helpful as he responds immediately to all questions.
Fantastic app - use it all the time, comprehensive and easy to setup. Google Calendar app catching on simple easy of use though.
I've used numerous planners/calendars but this beats the lot.  Been using it for some time now and it just seems to get better.  Brilliant.. üëç
I absolutely LOVE this app, however, every time I put in a new yearly event or change an event, the date changes, it will not stay on the date it is supposed to be on. PLEASE FIX!
replyContent: I am sorry that this problem occurred! Maybe it is a time zone issue. Please contact android@calengoo.com so that we can examined and fix the problem. Thank you very much!

content: The app and widget itself, its look is fantastic. But the app/widget's slowness, combined with its propensity to crash after a few taps into the settings is quite frustrating. Additionally, the widget does not update/refresh after syncing.  But if you click into the actual calendar APP, the new events are present. Only way I see to update the widget is to remove and add it back.... quite annoying.  2 stars since this app costs money yet only fulfills the bare minimum of usability.
replyContent: I am sorry that you have problems with the widget and the settings! Please contact android@calengoo.com so that I can help you to fix these problems. Thank you very much!

content: Still the best

Very customisable and integrates tasks well. Full sync with Google calendars and the opportunity to turn individual calendars off and on very easily. I like week view starting on Monday and jot many calendars provide this. All this means it can be tricky to get exactly right, but their support is second to none. Prompt and helpful they helped me tweak my settings.
Best I found 4 Android. Great UI and deep customizability. Great integration with work's calendaring.
Best calender app out there. My wife and I can keep track of each others appointments and schedules. Impossible to express just how much it helps me.
This calendar is so versatile and does so much that it is without doubt the best calendar app!

I've tried all the other strongly recommended calendar apps but they all fell short in multiple ways. Calengoo is the only one that does everything I need my calendar to do.  It's highly customisable without being confusing, has a *stellar* built-in snooze function, comes with multiple flexible and pretty-enough widgets, integrates very smoothly with Google Calendar and Tasks, and doesn't slow down my phone (Huawei Honor 6) at all.  Kudos. This is definitely one of my best Android purchases yet!

I have been using this for years. Viewing options are Great. Events show in blocks of time making it easy to find open slots. And overlapping events don't hide each other, like other apps. They are translucent in Calengoo. Love it.
This is the best calendar app I have found for Android.  I use Google at work and home and Calengoo integrates all my calendars and tasks.  Great job!
Use it on my phones and tablet. It is one of my five must have apps. And each update improves it, instead of breaking it (Google, take note.)

I've had Calengoo on four successive phones and it's worked flawlessly on all of them syncing with Google calendar. So convenient to update in one device and see it update online or other devices seamlessly. It just plain works so that I can too.

WONT SYNCH RELIABLY WITH GOOGLE CALENDAR AND MAKES EXCUSES FOR THAT  I just loaded Calengoo.  Every app should have a set up function so you can link it to your calendar (in my case my google calendar).  There is no set up function on this app.  I noted that Calengoo wasn't synching with my adroid phone.  I therefore went to accounts found that my phone was synching only with my "android calendar", whatever that is supposed to be.  I added Google as an account, and Google sent me an email confirming this fact.  I just added a test appointment to my google calendar.  It failed to appear.  I hit the "syn" button.  No change.    When you look in Settings under synch problems... you get a message saying that this ISN"T Calengoo's fault.    Quite unreliable and useless.
replyContent: I sent you a detailed email with instructions and explanations how to fix the problem 60 minutes after receiving your email. Did you read that email? You configured CalenGoo to sync via the Android calendar, which means the Android calendar performs the sync, not CalenGoo. Please just try my instructions to fix it or contact me again.

Having recently updated my CalenGoo App which I have enjoyed problem free for many years, I started to have a problem with the some of the views not wanting to initially load the events. replyContent: Just create a task for the first Sunday, then check "Recurring task" and select "weekly". If you have any further questions please contact android@calengoo.com.

Calengoo cannot be beaten. This is the best app there is when it comes to calendars and options. This one has so many options that it's simply amazing. I love options. I think options rule the world. What's great about it is that it caters to everyone and not a select few. Want no-frills and something basic? Fine, just leave it as is and it'll do that for you. Want super bells and whistles including voice reminders and custom colors and notifications and on and on? Fine, tweak it to your hearts content. I've been using it since long before I even had a smart phone. I used it on my Kindle Fire (first generation, bought brand new) which I used to carry around in my purse. I had a problem way back when and they immediately responded to it. Great support, great ideas, great implementation. You just can't beat it! Yes, I have the paid version and I'd pay it again if I could do it all over again. No, I'm not associated with them in any way. I'm just a multi-tasking woman who needs a good app and who is 500% satisfied with this app.

replyContent: Thank you very much! To get white text on black background in the edit screen just open "Settings", "Design" and set "Style" to "dark". If you have any problems please contact android@calengoo.com .

$6 is a little steep for an app these days, but Calengoo has so much functionality, it's well worth it. I have used many task apps and this is the first one I've found which offers full functionality AND truly syncs with Google. Recurrence for ToDo items has always been an issue with other apps I've tried. Because the task recurrence is stored in the event note, the recurrence is retained over all your devices. It is also retained if you have to reinstall the app. You can even check off a recurring task in Google Calendar and Calengoo will resolve the recurrence and Google will catch up. Brilliant. The interface is not quite as polished as some other calendar/ToDos but is immensely customizable. And almost my favorite part - there is an actual user manual on the website!

I have been using Calengoo on my HTC Rezound since 2012.  Prior to purchasing it, I tried a bunch of other Calendar program beginning with the built-in Android calendar.  The short version is that I found too many limitations and weaknesses with the other products.  Once I started using Calengoo, I was sold.  You can also configure everything in Calengoo, which is awesome!  Over the years I have emailed the developer with recommendations for improvements and to point out minor bugs (nothing that prevented the app from working correctly).  Most recently I noticed that the location font in my agenda widget was not changeable even though there was a setting for it.  I contacted the developer and Dominique responded right away as has been the case every time I have made contact.  He requested that I send my configuration file, which I did.  I got a response a day later stating that the problem had been found:  The font worked on the scrolling widget, but not the fixed widget.  He made the update and sent me the updated version, which works perfectly.  Total 5 stars to the developer!    Summarized thoughts: This is the best Calendar program available and for $5.99, you cannot go wrong!

I have been using calendar applications since the days of the Psion 3 pocket computer back in the early 90's.  Agenda for the Psion was and still is one of the best calendar applications ever. Still a great program for the Palm that syncs with the Palm Desktop or Outlook. Before I retired, I couldn't live without it. It literally ran my entire consulting business including billable hours, and generating invoices from Outlook. Unfortunately, Palm went belly up alsp. CESD wrote Pimlical for the Android and Windows. Another great program but very complex, and syncing does not work as well as DateBk/Outlook. That sent me looking for a new calendar program. After trying about 10 of them, CalenGoo is the one.  Calengoo is the best non-CESD calendar program out there. Spend the $5.99 and spend the time going through the excellent tutorial. CalenGoo has options for things you haven't even thought of but it will take time learning everything. You don't have to learn all the options but it's worth it.

replyContent: Hi! To access the menu please just long press the "recent apps" button (the button with the two rectangles). And to fix the problem with the widget (probably the agenda widget?) just turn "Scrollable widget" on in the settings that are displayed when adding the widget to your home screen. If you have further problems: email to android@calengoo.com

I have had several questions that I sent to the developer, and she is great at getting back to me promptly (allowing for time zone differences.) It is a TOTAL waste to have one app for calendar schedules and then go to another app for tasks...or have your scheduled events in one part of the app, but tasks in another. Tasks and events should always reside together within a certain calendar date...never separated...all in a single glance! Love the agenda view...each day lists my scheduled events, then below lists all tasks for the day (along with the tasks I didn't get to on previous days). My search is over! (Astrid who?).

In short: best calendar AND task app ever. Ever. IMO of course. Now long part. :-) And this is coming from somebody that loves to experiment with many apps just to see how they fare and work. Calendar apps are besides task aps probably most used on my both phones because of my heavy schedule (privately and for job). This is what the Google calendar & tasks should be; particularly tasks. Google tasks are relatively lame not allowing categorization or prioritization. Okay, Google does allow multiple lists which in a way can be used to categorize tasks, but YOU CAN ONLY VIEW ONE LIST AT A TIME. Aaaarrrgh. Calengoo uses lists (like Google), but has multiple views that allow the lists to be viewed in a consecutive stream in Tasks or combined in the Agenda view. You can also choose whether to show all tasks in the various calendar views. AND you can prioritize tasks in a 1-5 format and they're displayed accordingly. Excellent implementation.   So now my Google tasks and calendar are extremely usable on my Android phone and Android Kindle, but the implementation on my real laptop computer running Windows is still the same lame implementation of the native Google apps. Until i came across a program called Bluestack which I installed (free) on my laptop. Bluestack allows you to run your Android apps on a Windows based computer, so now I have the functionality of Calengoo on my Windows laptop - does it get any better?

A good calendar is one of the most important features for me and stock calendars on any platform are all rubbish. So I always try out 3rd party apps as soon as I change platforms. This is my first Android device and finding this calendar was a godsend. It has all the functions and features you're likely to need, has a logical layout and very easy to use.The week view is particularly good with the days spread out horizontally rather than the more usual grid formation and events are shown in individual vertical blocks. This layout is much easier to read at a glance. There's loads of options to personalise it but it's not overburdened with gimmicks (except perhaps for too many widgets!). It will sync directly with Google Calendar and if you use multiple calendars on Google with different colours for each calendar this app will sync them all and display the same colours on the handset. It works flawlessly and syncing to Google Calendar works both ways almost instantly. If you or your company use Google Calender this is the perfect handset app. I've tried many calendars on loads of different platforms but this is the best I've used. Great value.

Two things make this app stand out from the crowd.   First, other calendar apps on Android sync with Google calendar via the phone's built-in Android calendar. But there is a huge limitation that is not widely known -- Android's calendar syncs only about 30 days into the past, and only about 1 year into the future. So if today (late April, 2012) I go into Gcal on my browser, and enter a new event for (say) August 2013, that event WILL NOT sync down to my phone (at least, not until about August this year, when it's about a year away). This is useless for someone like me, who needs to plan things way in advance. Calengoo gets around this limitation by allowing the user to instead sync DIRECTLY with Google calendar -- all events (past & future) are synced.  Second, I am a heavy user of tasks. Calengoo syncs to Google tasks, but I don't much like them (too rudimentary). Calengoo does NOT sync to Toodledo (at least, as of today) BUT it has "floating" events that can be checked off. These work VERY well in place of tasks. I set up a new calendar on Google, and I use it exclusively for these floating events. You can set times, check them off and drag & drop to rearrange them. Great !!

I have spent the last 3 days testing many free and not so free calendar and task management combinations on my recently acquired Samsung Galaxy Nexus (Android version 4.0.2). This is by far the best that I have encountered. My requirements were simple: 1. Sync my Google calendars AND tasks. 2. Allow task alerts days/weeks/months before a task is due. 3. Show tasks in the calendar views. 4. A widget that presents a homepage summary of upcoming events and tasks. I got this and much more with Calengoo. First of all, it works with Ice Cream Sandwich (many did not)! Calengoo meet all of my requirements and provided useful capabilities that I did not know I wanted (if not needed). For me, Calengoo's greatest strength is its configurability. (This might also be considered a weakness by some folks.) Whenever I thought something was missing, digging down into the settings resulted in just the display that I wanted. Unlike many of the apps I tried, the author has a nice website that actually explains the operation of the program (occasionally, iPhone oriented or different version). Avoid frustration - read the info on syncing Android & Google calendars & tasks. Overall, well worth the money.
